 Wishes Inn

31
00:03:30,964 --> 00:03:34,184
- Here are two bowls of rice soup. 
- Okay.

32
00:03:34,184 --> 00:03:38,714
Here is Hanyang's most delicious rice soup.

33
00:03:40,794 --> 00:03:43,104
Enjoy your drink.

34
00:03:43,104 --> 00:03:48,074
 Emergency Funds, Loans

35
00:03:49,024 --> 00:03:52,524
- Here it is. 
- Oh, thank you!

36
00:03:52,524 --> 00:03:54,304
And...

37
00:03:55,394 --> 00:03:58,174
I'll give you condolence money in advance.

38
00:03:58,174 --> 00:04:02,454
On your way home, you should prepare a good coffin.

39
00:04:04,864 --> 00:04:08,164
- Thank you, Innkeeper. 
- I hope the funeral goes well.

40
00:04:08,164 --> 00:04:10,254
Thank you.

41
00:04:16,104 --> 00:04:18,864
Have a cool drink.

42
00:04:23,434 --> 00:04:29,324
At first, you looked like the youngest daughter of a fallen noble family,

43
00:04:29,324 --> 00:04:33,994
but you completely look like a maidservant now.

44
00:04:34,754 --> 00:04:39,424
If I relied on my rights as a princess, whom could I comfortably ask for help?

45
00:04:39,424 --> 00:04:41,584
What kind of princess would be doing this?

46
00:04:41,584 --> 00:04:46,324
That's why I did it. Because someone has to do what others cannot.

47
00:04:46,324 --> 00:04:48,094
Prin–

48
00:04:52,167 --> 00:04:55,354
If there are three zeros,

49
00:04:55,354 --> 00:04:57,734
If there are three zeros...

50
00:04:59,784 --> 00:05:02,314
How much was it?

51
00:05:05,294 --> 00:05:09,904
You should do like this, My Lady!

52
00:05:09,904 --> 00:05:11,984
Enjoy your drink.

53
00:05:17,274 --> 00:05:19,804
Next person.

54
00:05:20,674 --> 00:05:24,244
 Merchant Jang's Plum Wine Bar

55
00:05:28,804 --> 00:05:31,604
 Plum Wine

56
00:05:38,404 --> 00:05:41,004
This tastes awful. This tastes awful.

57
00:05:41,004 --> 00:05:46,014
The plum wine from the street stall over there smelled so good.

58
00:05:46,014 --> 00:05:48,614
But what's wrong with this?

59
00:06:02,134 --> 00:06:03,714
What?

60
00:06:22,764 --> 00:06:27,384
Aigoo. Here is plum wine.

61
00:06:27,384 --> 00:06:30,964
This smells amazing.

62
00:06:30,964 --> 00:06:33,704
Here, here.

63
00:06:33,704 --> 00:06:36,464
Enjoy your drink. Yes, yes, coming!

64
00:06:36,464 --> 00:06:38,724
It smells good.

65
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:44,424
- Please enjoy it and spread the word. 
- Hey.

66
00:06:44,424 --> 00:06:46,304
Yes, yes.

67
00:06:48,591 --> 00:06:52,254
How dare you sell plum wine, plum wine, plum wine?

68
00:06:52,254 --> 00:06:55,444
- Aigoo, my son.
 - Get out of the way, old lady.

69
00:06:55,444 --> 00:06:58,134
Mother! Mother! Mother!

70
00:06:58,134 --> 00:07:00,330
What the hell are you looking at!

71
00:07:00,624 --> 00:07:03,814
Hurry up and run away! Go!

72
00:07:03,814 --> 00:07:07,484
Go! Hurry up and go!

73
00:07:07,484 --> 00:07:10,824
Hey, get him! Get him!

74
00:07:23,724 --> 00:07:25,764
What are you doing?

75
00:07:55,084 --> 00:07:56,764
Yum, yum.

76
00:07:56,764 --> 00:07:58,584
Aren't you going to eat it?

77
00:08:00,844 --> 00:08:04,564
Please hide me. If I get caught, I will be beaten to death.

78
00:08:04,564 --> 00:08:08,084
Oh, you should not be beaten. Go hide behind my donkey.

79
00:08:08,084 --> 00:08:12,284
Where are you, knave? Come out!

80
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:14,680
Hey!

81
00:08:14,684 --> 00:08:18,024
More, more. Go to the corner.

82
00:08:19,634 --> 00:08:21,964
Where is he? Shit!

83
00:08:21,964 --> 00:08:25,854
Hey, didn't you see the guy who ran away here?

84
00:08:33,190 --> 00:08:35,680
Hey, catch him quickly!

85
00:08:36,674 --> 00:08:38,964
There he is!

86
00:08:54,467 --> 00:08:59,604
You should've given me a commission and obeyed me when I asked nicely.

87
00:08:59,604 --> 00:09:02,294
How dare you sell plum wine without our merchant's permission?

88
00:09:02,294 --> 00:09:04,304
You thieves!

89
00:09:04,304 --> 00:09:08,234
I set up first, and I make my own wine out of my own rice.

90
00:09:08,234 --> 00:09:12,154
Who gives you the right to take a commission from me?

91
00:09:13,884 --> 00:09:16,194
Stand up.

92
00:09:16,194 --> 00:09:20,124
You still don't understand what I am saying.

93
00:09:22,004 --> 00:09:23,894
Stand up.

94
00:09:25,874 --> 00:09:27,784
Stop it!

95
00:09:29,084 --> 00:09:30,784
What is this?

96
00:09:33,624 --> 00:09:35,284
Who are you?

97
00:09:36,204 --> 00:09:37,964
What is that?

98
00:09:51,854 --> 00:09:53,394
What?

99
00:09:54,974 --> 00:09:56,584
Let's go!

100
00:09:57,604 --> 00:09:59,244
Boss.

101
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:04,854
What are you doing in the backyard of someone's inn?

102
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:06,584
What is this?

103
00:10:06,584 --> 00:10:08,394
Who is she?

104
00:10:08,394 --> 00:10:12,304
She is the owner of Wishes Inn, Inkeeper Hong.

105
00:10:14,284 --> 00:10:17,344
Salted shrimp, liquor jars,

106
00:10:17,344 --> 00:10:19,434
broken and ruined troughs...

107
00:10:19,434 --> 00:10:23,364
Even at a rough estimate, the damage seems to be at least 50 nyang.

108
00:10:23,364 --> 00:10:26,854
Are you standing here to compensate me for them?

109
00:10:39,614 --> 00:10:41,254
Let's go.

110
00:10:44,724 --> 00:10:46,824
Consider yourself lucky.

111
00:10:50,474 --> 00:10:54,104
Aigoo. What should I do with all these?

112
00:10:58,674 --> 00:11:01,584
It is okay. Just go.

113
00:11:04,424 --> 00:11:07,794
- Excuse me? 
- I was trying to scare them.

114
00:11:07,794 --> 00:11:10,344
Do not worry, and just go.

115
00:11:10,344 --> 00:11:13,974
But what about this precious thing?

116
00:11:15,964 --> 00:11:20,354
Thank you. Thank you, So Won.

117
00:11:20,354 --> 00:11:22,594
Thank you.

118
00:11:28,184 --> 00:11:30,884
Who are those rogues?

119
00:11:30,884 --> 00:11:32,794
They belong to Merchant Jang.

120
00:11:32,794 --> 00:11:36,254
- Find out what is going on. 
- Yes.

121
00:11:49,224 --> 00:11:54,224
A drink you cannot sell is worse than wastewater.

122
00:12:01,167 --> 00:12:04,314
Why is the world so heartless to me?

123
00:12:04,314 --> 00:12:08,534
Do you want me to starve to death like this?

124
00:12:32,814 --> 00:12:36,234
 Hire an attorney for legal problems

125
00:12:38,004 --> 00:12:41,004
 Advance Payment Welcome

126
00:12:42,934 --> 00:12:44,884
Nice to meet you again.

127
00:12:45,674 --> 00:12:49,044
Are you a real attorney?

128
00:12:49,044 --> 00:12:54,224
Right. I am attorney Kang Han Su.

129
00:12:54,224 --> 00:12:56,774
What a rotten guy!

130
00:12:58,504 --> 00:13:02,264
Why do you get slapped at the Han River and vent your anger at the Nakdong River?  (i.e. why shift the blame to me?)

131
00:13:03,694 --> 00:13:07,374
Is it not human nature to help people in need?

132
00:13:07,374 --> 00:13:11,174
But you, the so-called attorney...

133
00:13:11,174 --> 00:13:14,604
That was before I was hired as an attorney.

134
00:13:14,604 --> 00:13:16,694
I...

135
00:13:16,694 --> 00:13:20,694
only work when I am paid.

136
00:13:21,734 --> 00:13:25,554
- What? 
- Are you upset? Is it unfair?

137
00:13:25,554 --> 00:13:27,394
Then file a lawsuit.

138
00:13:27,394 --> 00:13:31,994
It would be quicker to rely on the law than on human nature.

139
00:13:31,994 --> 00:13:37,344
I would rather drown with my nose in the dishwater than trust a guy like you.

140
00:13:40,524 --> 00:13:43,324
Which dish are you going to stick your nose in?

141
00:13:46,074 --> 00:13:48,014
Crazy bastard!

142
00:13:55,894 --> 00:13:59,424
Or is there another way for you to make a living?

143
00:14:01,214 --> 00:14:06,674
Try to cry and worry like that for a hundred days. See who will listen to you.

144
00:14:06,674 --> 00:14:12,424
I tried to save the people whom the king has abandoned, yet you try to punch me?

145
00:14:12,424 --> 00:14:16,634
That's why you live your whole life like that!

146
00:14:18,234 --> 00:14:22,184
- Honey! 
- Father!

147
00:14:22,184 --> 00:14:24,414
Why did you come all the way here?

148
00:14:24,414 --> 00:14:26,554
What happened to your face?

149
00:14:26,554 --> 00:14:30,084
Let's go home. Let's go.

150
00:14:31,064 --> 00:14:32,594
Ouch.

151
00:14:32,594 --> 00:14:34,954
You! Come in!

152
00:14:34,954 --> 00:14:38,000
- Why are you hitting me, too?
 - Hurry!

153
00:14:39,064 --> 00:14:41,394
Hey, hey, hey!

154
00:14:42,914 --> 00:14:45,584
Are you out of your mind or not?

155
00:14:45,584 --> 00:14:48,144
It took so much to bring in that client!

156
00:14:48,144 --> 00:14:50,394
He still has a long way to go.

157
00:14:50,394 --> 00:14:55,814
How many people have we seen who rush to file a lawsuit and give up so easily?

158
00:14:57,814 --> 00:15:03,734
So we have to push him to the extreme limit so

159
00:15:03,734 --> 00:15:08,504
he will not be swayed by any variables, temptations, or fears.

160
00:15:08,504 --> 00:15:12,034
E-Extreme limit?

161
00:15:12,034 --> 00:15:15,984
Sir, I'm Park, who sells plum wine. Please help me with the lawsuit—

162
00:15:15,984 --> 00:15:19,354
No, no. Go find somewhere else.

163
00:15:22,704 --> 00:15:25,694
Attorney Sir, I need to sue Merchant Jang...

164
00:15:25,694 --> 00:15:26,744
Oh, I can't, I can't.

165
00:15:26,744 --> 00:15:28,494
We cannot defeat Merchant Jang.

166
00:15:28,494 --> 00:15:30,674
Please do not do this here.

167
00:16:17,504 --> 00:16:20,734
 He will definitely come back.

168
00:16:20,734 --> 00:16:23,714
 He will not survive unless he comes back here.

169
00:16:35,764 --> 00:16:38,674
 So are you leaving Hanyang?

170
00:16:42,004 --> 00:16:45,124
This is your hometown, where you were born and raised.

171
00:16:45,124 --> 00:16:47,734
What about the work you have been doing all your life?

172
00:16:47,734 --> 00:16:51,284
There's no place to rely on, no place to appeal.

173
00:16:52,234 --> 00:16:55,304
What's the point of a hometown?

174
00:16:58,314 --> 00:17:03,024
I'm sure there is a way. If you wait a little longer...

175
00:17:03,024 --> 00:17:05,824
I have endured enough, so it is okay.

176
00:17:05,824 --> 00:17:09,704
Even if I want to file charges, the only attorney willing to take it is

177
00:17:09,704 --> 00:17:12,394
only that scumbag, Kang Han Su.

178
00:17:12,394 --> 00:17:15,214
I will be sure to pay you back this money.

179
00:17:15,994 --> 00:17:18,264
Thank you, So Won.

180
00:18:39,774 --> 00:18:44,284
Your Majesty, Princess Yeon Ju is here.

181
00:18:50,234 --> 00:18:53,034
- Your Majesty. 
 - Sister.

182
00:18:54,064 --> 00:18:57,124
Where did all these carp come from?

183
00:18:57,124 --> 00:18:59,904
I guess people caught them and brought them here.

184
00:18:59,904 --> 00:19:04,764
People like to catch and trap something, don't they?

185
00:19:04,764 --> 00:19:09,594
I'm no different than an unlucky carp who is trapped.

186
00:19:18,224 --> 00:19:20,154
Then I was lucky.

187
00:19:20,154 --> 00:19:26,054
I got to leave the palace and live freely, thanks to our father's early passing.

188
00:19:26,874 --> 00:19:28,834
That's not what I meant.

189
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:31,154
I know. I was just joking.

190
00:19:31,154 --> 00:19:34,504
Anyway, I cannot joke with you, Your Majesty.

191
00:19:37,254 --> 00:19:41,794
You can joke about everything but the throne.

192
00:19:42,974 --> 00:19:48,384
It's the throne my uncle ascended so hurriedly that he even overthrew my older brother.

193
00:19:49,814 --> 00:19:52,114
It's a bed of thorns,

194
00:19:52,114 --> 00:19:54,884
so I cannot face you nor the grand prince.

195
00:19:55,634 --> 00:19:59,724
Why do you often summon me when you say you cannot face me?

196
00:19:59,724 --> 00:20:04,644
That is because no one else tells me real stories besides you.

197
00:20:06,564 --> 00:20:11,374
Now, what other fun stories are you going to tell me today?

198
00:20:19,914 --> 00:20:22,344
This has a deep and intense smell.

199
00:20:22,344 --> 00:20:24,644
Yes, this is wine.

200
00:20:24,644 --> 00:20:29,714
It's plum wine made with a secret method that has been handed down for three generations.

201
00:20:33,744 --> 00:20:36,144
Is it not a waste to enjoy it alone?

202
00:20:36,144 --> 00:20:38,764
Then go ahead, Sister.

203
00:20:38,764 --> 00:20:43,564
The people. I want to introduce this taste to them as well.

204
00:20:43,564 --> 00:20:47,824
But the city's alcohol trade is held tightly by Merchant Jang.

205
00:20:47,824 --> 00:20:53,754
Therefore, small merchants like Park cannot do business freely but rather get kicked out.

206
00:20:53,754 --> 00:20:55,794
To them, power is the law.

207
00:20:55,794 --> 00:21:00,654
That is why we need to clear the way for small merchants to run businesses freely.

208
00:21:01,414 --> 00:21:03,504
We should do that.

209
00:21:03,504 --> 00:21:07,264
Even though I am under a regency, I am still the king.

210
00:21:07,264 --> 00:21:10,044
I can handle something like this without a problem.

211
00:21:12,534 --> 00:21:14,434
Then I will finish the rest of your drink.

212
00:21:14,434 --> 00:21:16,434
Do you want some more?

213
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:21,570
 Attorney for Hire / Legal Department / Kang Han Su

214
00:21:21,570 --> 00:21:23,884
Here. I am attorney Kang Han Su.

215
00:21:23,884 --> 00:21:27,674
I am attorney Kang Han Su. Just tell me if you experience something unfair and bitter.

216
00:21:27,674 --> 00:21:30,284
We will definitely win. Please trust me.

217
00:21:30,284 --> 00:21:33,894
Get one nyang and earn ten nyang. I am attorney Kang Han Su!

218
00:21:33,894 --> 00:21:38,014
Just tell me something that is unfair and bitter. We will definitely win.

219
00:21:38,014 --> 00:21:40,624
- Attorney? 
- On behalf of your siblings, uncles, nephews,

220
00:21:40,624 --> 00:21:42,974
in-laws, and relatives, I will file a lawsuit.

221
00:21:42,974 --> 00:21:45,794
We will definitely win. I am attorney Kang Han Su!

222
00:21:45,794 --> 00:21:48,804
I am attorney Kang Han Su!

223
00:22:05,254 --> 00:22:07,954
Except for the cases where the slave accuses the owner, the son accuses the father,

224
00:22:07,954 --> 00:22:10,584
and the wife accuses the husband, we will settle everything.

225
00:22:10,584 --> 00:22:13,694
Here is one for you, My Lady!

226
00:22:13,694 --> 00:22:18,284
Here. I am attorney Kang Han Su. We will definitely win!

